It is meant to be performant and fully functioning with low- and high-level SDKs, while minimizing dependencies and providing platform portability (Windows, OSX, Linux, and mobile).
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Summary of changes made in this release of the package.
FeedPackage.Summary: v120 and v140 binary packages along with header files. No custom memory management. Standard Compiler flags used. For more info, see https://github.com/aws/aws-sdk-cpp/blob/master/README.md

EntityFramework Profiler is a real-time visual debugger allowing a development team to gain valuable insight and perspective into their usage of EntityFramework. The product is architected with input coming from many top industry leaders within the OR/M community. Alerts are presented in a concise code-review manner indicating patterns of misuse by your application. To streamline your efforts to correct the misuse, we provide links to the problematic code section that triggered the alert.
We provide a 30 day trial to download and see for yourself, the value you will receive with your purchase of EntityFramework Profiler.

The product is architected with input coming from many top industry leaders within the OR/M community. Alerts are presented in a concise code-review manner indicating patterns of misuse by your application. To streamline your efforts to correct the misuse, we provide links to the problematic code section that triggered the alert.
We provide a 30 day trial to download and see for yourself, the value you will receive with your purchase of EntityFramework Profiler.

FeedPackage.Tags: EntityFramework Profiler Prof Production EFProf

FeedPackage.Description: Amazon Elasticsearch Service Client for the AWS SDK for C++. AWS SDK for C++ provides a modern C++ (version C++ 11 or later) interface for Amazon Web Services (AWS). FeedPackage.Description:
Look at your MVC app.
Now back to me.
Now go back at your MVC App. It's missing a nice standard JSON Api wrapper .. even for errors? Sadly, it's not using me, but it could be using me!
Look down ... back up. Where are you? You're at your desk. With the NuGet package you could use.
What's in your hand? Back at me.
I have it. It's an oyster with two tickets to the conference you love.
Look again! The tickets are now Apple Airs!
Anything is possible when you're using this NuGet package in your MVC App.
I'm on a horse.
FeedPackage.Summary: A simple toolkit that enables you to have a standard JSON Api response. Also contains a bonus JsonErrorHandler :)
FeedPackage.Title: MagicalUnicornMvcApiJsonToolkit

FeedPackage.Description:
Would you like your ASP.NET MVC web application to handle both 404 Not Found errors and 500 Server Errors (and everything in between?).
Hells yeah, you do! I do! Unicorns do!
So this little nuget package is for you -> it's sets up some settings in your web.config & global.asax. It adds a controller with the appropriate views and off you go :)
Or you can do it manually yourself: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/619895/how-can-i-properly-handle-404-in-asp-net-mvc/7499406#7499406
Shout out to David Fowler for the suggestion, while in SignalR. :)
FeedPackage.Summary: Wire up 404 Not Found errors and 500 Server Errors (and any other Http errors) for an ASP.NET MVC web application.
FeedPackage.Tags: asp.net-mvc magical-unicorn error-handling 404-not-found 500-server-error
FeedPackage.Title: MagicalUnicornMvcErrorToolkit

FeedPackage.Description:
Me: Sons of Djorks, I am Magical Unicorn - Mvc Request Header Authorization Attribute.
You: You're 7 GitHub projects, tall ...
Me: Yes, I've heard. Kills Meme's by the hundreads and if he were here he'd consume Rails with fireballs from his eyes and bolts of lightning from his arse. I AM MGMRHAA. And I see a whole army of my programmers here in defiance of missing-framework titty sprinkle authorization functionality.
Someone else: Program? Against that? No, we Cancel; and we live.
Me: Aye, program and you may die. Cancel and you'll live -- at least a while. And dying in your beds many years from now .. would you be willing to trade all the days from this day, to that, for one chance .. .just one change to back here and tell our enemy-languages that they make take our code, but they'll never take our freedom!!!
All: Freedome forever!

FeedPackage.Description: Adds events for entity inserting, inserted, updating, updated, deleting, and deleted. If you need support for EF5, check out my package 'EntityFrameworkCodeFirstTriggers'
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Added an unobtrusive way to support triggers. This is necessary in a situation where you don't have control of what your context class inherits from, like EF DB-first or Microsoft.AspNet.Identity.EntityFramework.IdentityDbContext<...> which inherits from DbContext. The only functionality lost is a strong-typed reference to the DbContext-derived class in the trigger delegates. I added a helper method to Entry struct to clean that up a bit. Check out the usage example on the project home page!

FeedPackage.Description: Every .NET developer needs a .NET assembly browser. We do not need such tool for everyday usage. FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Rustemsoft represents freeware Refractor .NET assembly browser and decompiler that should be good for your .NET development needs. Also Rustemsoft Skater .NET Obfuscator is equipped with .NET assembly browser and decompiler interface since ver5.0. Freeware and Demo versions of Skater .NET obfuscator include the fully functional .NET code browser interface. RustemSoft does not charge for the .NET assembly browser and decompiler. Rustemsoft does not plan to charge for that.
